content:
The Overall Performance tab shows key summary metrics for model quality. 

Navigate to the Overall Performance Tab by clicking Model Evaluation, then Overall Performance in the Performance section.

Summary Metrics:
AUC (Area Under the Curve): measures the logistic model's rate of correct classification.
Range: 0.5 (random guessing) to 1.0 (100% correct)
GINI Index: measures how closely this classification model performs to a theoretically best possible model.
Range: 0 (random guessing) to 1 (exact match)
MCC (Matthews Correlation Coefficient): measures the quality of a classification model, providing an even representation of the confusion matrix.
Range: -1 (wrongly predicted class every time), 0 (random guessing), +1 (correctly predicted class every time)

Accuracy Analysis:
Accuracy = (TP + TN) / Total # of Predictions
True Positive Rate: correctly scores records as true n% of the time
True Negative Rate: correctly scores records as false n% of the time
False Positive Rate: incorrectly scores records as true n% of the time
False Negative Rate: incorrectly scores records as false n% of the time
Threshold Value: represents the tradeoff between true positive and false positive rates.
title: Evaluating Model Quality with Overall Performance Tab
